cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "uniprot-mcp: A Model Context Protocol server for the UniProt protein knowledgebase"
abstract: >-
  uniprot-mcp is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that exposes the
  UniProt protein knowledgebase to LLM-driven agents such as Claude. It
  ships 38 read-only tools across eight families: search and lookup;
  structural cross-references (PDB, AlphaFold per-residue pLDDT bands);
  variants and disease (ClinVar bridge, position-aware variant lookup,
  OMIM); position-aware features (active sites, signal peptides, modified
  residues, natural variants); composition dossier (sequence chemistry,
  drug-target context, disease associations); orthology; a local
  provenance cache with replay; and per-query provenance verification.
  Every response carries a verifiable provenance record - the UniProt
  release number, release date, retrieval timestamp, resolved URL, and
  a release-aware SHA-256 digest of the canonical response bytes. Strict
  accession and identifier validation, retry and back-off, snapshot-tested
  formatters, agent-safe error envelopes, and a cross-origin allowlist
  policy round out the operational hardening. Distributed on PyPI as
  "uniprot-mcp-server"; the installed console script and MCP server
  identity are both "uniprot-mcp".
